                <h2>Start Early.</h2>
                <p>Starting early is very important. it is much easier to maintain a high GPA than to recover one that has tanked. Starting early is key and for those about starting junior year, senior year or college, start early. But what if you're already getting a late start? If you are nearing the end of your junior year, or already a senior in high school or college, you want to focus instead on raising your GPA making it better than it's now. It's time to buckle up, checkGPA will assist you in calculating, maintaining and raising your GPA.</p>

                <h2>Ways to Raise Your GPA.</h2>
                <p>Starting early form the foundation of a strong GPA. In addition, here are practical tips for raising your GPA. </p>
                <div class="unorder-list">
                    <ul>

                        <li>
                            <h2 class="point-h2">Ensure you attend every class.</h2>
                        </li>
                        <p>People take attending classes for granted especially if there will be no class attendance. Also College students try to justify skipping class—especially if the professor makes the lecture slides available online—but if you're interested in a solid GPA, discipline yourself to show up. Attending class plays a huge role in maintaing and raising your GPA.</p>
                        <p>For example. Daniel a bright, hard-working student in college decided in semester A that he will not be going for English classes, thinking he will be able to easily ace the course. He said "It is just english i can write it in my sleep."</p>
                        <p>Look at Daniel result for semester A.</p>
